sub_title: Program Manager at Community Partners International
summary: Within eight years of working in Myanmar development sector, I have worked with various organizations in the fields of policy, health, education and social empowerment. The roles range from volunteer English teacher, medical officer, project coordinator, system analyst to program manager, dealing with different stakeholder groups such as farmers from Kaw Hmu township, religious leaders from Chin State, IDP camp residences from Kachin State, business leaders and developers in the field of hospitality and catering and healthcare managers from Ministry of Health and Sports, to name a few. My known strength of interpersonal skills, facilitation and negotiation skills  has ensured me to engage with right people, at the right place at the right time for successful implementation of various jobs that I've undertaken.
